# Cursor Rules — ui-ux.mdc

## UI goals
Create a modern, minimal, mobile-first interface with clear visual hierarchy
and predictable interactions.

## Mobile-first
- Design for mobile first (360–430px).
- Touch targets >= 44px.
- Use vertical layouts and avoid dense UI.

## Design system
- Use a consistent spacing system (8px base).
- Reuse shared components: Button, Input, Card, Tabs, BottomNav, Modal.
- Keep border radius, shadows, and typography consistent.

## Accessibility (mandatory)
- Semantic HTML elements.
- Proper labels for inputs.
- `aria-label` for icon buttons.
- Visible focus states.
- Keyboard navigation for modals and forms.

## UI states (mandatory)
Every screen must support:
- Loading (skeleton)
- Empty state
- Error state (clear, human-readable)
- Success feedback

## Performance
- Optimize images.
- Avoid layout shifts.
- Keep animations subtle and optional.

## Content tone
- Clear, short text.
- Avoid jargon.
- Errors must explain what went wrong and what to do next.
